<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-04-25T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-04-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="1551" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1551">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 819.00/387.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams.—Extracts.—Paraphrases.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Panama</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-04-25">
                                    <hi rend="italic">April 25, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>The Porras party committee has left a petition, which goes in the pouch
                            tomorrow, requesting supervision by the United States of the
                            registration of voters, in view of the grave electoral situation and in
                            order to give proper guaranties to their opponents; such supervision to
                            begin as soon as possible, as registration will close on May 15. The
                            petition also requests supervision by the United States of both the
                            municipal elections (June 30) and the presidential elections (July 14
                            and August 2). Numerous supporting documents accompany the petition,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Dodge</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>